We are not held from our destinies by trials and tribulations …. but by clearer paths to lesser goals 

for most of us it’s not bad things that keep us stuck in life

many times our hands are so full with what we have, that we have no room to accept what God is trying to give us 

Where you are right now is not permanent 

What you are going through won’t defeat you 

Let go of your limitations, your doubts and your unbelief, let go of average and ordinary, of comfort and complacency and GET READY!! 

You’re about to LEVEL UP infront of some folks

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Ian Prukner on July 08, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, beard, standing and outdoors.

node.text:
4 things that HURT now but PAY OFF later ….

1. Discipline- 
discipline is inescapable, we will either discipline ourselves or someone else will discipline us …

Choosing what you want most over what you want now is a  skill absent in virtually everybody. Will you accept short-term pain for long-term gain?

2. Self Improvement -
Nobody’s holding a gun to your head forcing you to get better… but things don’t get better until we get better.

Our very best thinking belief systems and habits have gotten us exactly what we have now if we ever want to have more, do more, and accomplish more, we first must become more…  internal victories will always proceed external ones

3.  Investing - 
Investing at the core whether it’s money, or time, or self-improvement is about holding back some of what you have now to invest into your future self

But here’s the truth: if you don’t invest in you why should anybody else. YOU have been and will always be your best investment.. You need to invest in your future because one day you’re gonna have to live there.

4. Self Control 
it’s easy today to be offended, to be angry, to give somebody a piece of your mind…. DON’T…. it’s a trap 

great leaders never lose their self control they always play it close to the vest…. 

When we don’t have self control we are out of control and end up being controlled by others or circumstances

keep your power, become  unoffendable, stay in control 

DROP A 🙌🏻🙌🏻 If this spoke to you

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Ian Prukner in Pruk Ranch. May be an image of 1 person, beard, standing and indoor.

node.text:
LONG POST ALERT 

Distraction= Destruction

most people are not incapable of achieving their dreams, they are just unfocused

most of the time our lives are not held back by bad things , but by good things in place of the best things 
 
the TRUTH is this: we could be doing big things if we weren’t so busy doing small ones 

 Our ability to focus for long periods of time on the most important things will determine the level of success we achieve

so here’s my top 3 steps to staying focused: 

1. Don’t over commit: when you say yes to something you say no to something else… make sure that you have space in your life to say yes to the things that move the needle 

2. Do the most important things early and consistently, that way if you only get a little bit done every day you’ve gotten the most important things done

3. Get clear about what you want- because when you don’t know where you’re going any path will get you there. we can avoid the rabbit trails of life by having a clear and compelling vision of our destination.

the best part is this :  FOCUS IS FREE
 it requires no talent and no cost to focus

so stop saying yes to everything so you have the time and energy to focus on the best things 

DROP A 💯 if this spoke to you

GOD WANTS TO TAKE YOUR LIFE TO A COMPLETELY NEW LEVEL

node.text:
I saw this view 10,000 times in my mind before I ever lived it 

every time someone said no I saw it 

every time someone quit, I saw it 

every time someone changed their mind, talked bad about me, promised me something that didn’t come through… I saw it 

See, You got to KEEP THE VISION infront of you… ALWAYS 

Why? 

Because you will either see the Vision or the Obstacle

they are BOTH there all the time …. but which one you see , experience, and live will be determined by your focus…

are you focused on the vision or the problem? 

your going to have problems setbacks struggles and issues… the question is what will you have to show for it? 

will you have  million dollar views or millions of excuses ? it’s your choice 

what you think about you will eventually bring about so GET CLEAR about what you want why you want it and then GO GET IT !!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Ian Prukner on June 25, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and suit.

node.text:
4 things that it takes to win:

1.  Total committment - 

there is but one level of committment : TOTAL. The price of success must be paid upfront and in full. 

2. Unparalleled work ethic -

hard work beats talent when talent doesn’t work hard. Work ethic is a choice , we’ve got to be the hardest worker in the room 

3.  Relentless self improvement - 

 what it takes to win is not something outside of us, but rather  something Inside of us.  If we are ever to have more, we must first become more. We can’t stay the same and expect our world to change 

4.  Mental Toughness -

You simply don’t win with your head, you win with your heart. so much of winning is holding on a little longer than everyone else. internal victories will always precede external ones 

What I love about winning is that ANYONE can win; not everyone will win, but everyone CAN win: why? 
because winning is not a talent winning is a CHOICE !!

node.text:
@jessica_prukner and I will be celebrating 16 years next week !!🔥🔥

we started our marriage with this advice from one of my mentors…

“All marriages are bad; but some people make them good”

what he meant was this: as people, we are inherently selfish … we want what we want 
 
marriage on the other hand is about unselfish.. it’s about two  people coming together in an agreement to put US over ME… to live unselfishly 

the truth is this: IT’S HARD WORK

it requires time, communication, effort, thoughtfulness, committment and grace 

it also requires us to understand that success in marriage is not about FINDING the right person… it’s about us BEING the right person.

No matter where you are in your relationship right now you have the choice to BE the right person

LOVE IS A DECISION it’s not a feeling 

out of one of the hardest times in our marriage, a time that required us to refocus on eachother, on putting eachother first and on repriorotzing our lives, our annual marriage retreat : the Relentless Pursuit Marriage Retreat Was birthed.

we felt a burden to give couples the tools, resources and support we wished we had along the way to make their relationships great

on August 15th-  40
couples from around the world will join us LIVE @prukranch to spend a day refocusing , recommitting and re igniting their dreams and relationships 

there’s only a handful of spots left.. 
the link is in my bio so check it out 

and remember : God wants you to win, he wants your marriage to succeed and he has a BIG plan for your family
